\color blue
a scale parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta=1.2$
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Å
\begin_inset Formula $^{-1}$
\end_inset

,
\color inherit
 is evaluated together with the electron charge density 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\text{e}}$
\end_inset

 on a uniform Cartesian grid.
 The Poisson equation is then solved for the net neutral charge distribution
 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\text{e}}+n_{\text{n}}^{\prime}$
\end_inset

 by the same techniques as for the solvent charge density 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\text{v}}$
\end_inset

